<DOC><DOCNO> AP890910-0018 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-10-89 1218EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-TyphoonSarah 1stLd-Writethru   09-10 0170</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Typhoon Sarah, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0638,0171</SECOND><HEAD>Typhoon Kills Eight in the Philippines</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: Recasts first two grafs to delete redundancy. Pick up 3rd pvs,``Civil Defense...'</HEAD><DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Typhoon Sarah caused flooding andlandslides in the northern Philippines that left eight people dead,nine missing and more than 1,000 families homeless, officials saidSunday.   By midday, the storm was centered 50 miles southeast of Bascotown at the northern tip of the Philippines and was headed towardsouthern Taiwan, the weather bureau said. Sarah, with top winds of72 mph, produced heavy rain.   Civil Defense and Red Cross officials, who provided the damagereport, said two children drowned Saturday in Ilocos Sur provinceafter their house was swept away by floodwaters. An unidentified manalso drowned in the province.   In the mountain province of Benguet, landslides killed fivepeople in Banagan village, the officials said.   Landslides cut off all roads leading to the northern resort cityof Baguio for several hours but were cleared Sunday, rescueofficials said.</TEXT></DOC>